.el .ds Aq '
.TH rom-weaver-probe 1  "rom-weaver-probe "
.SH NAME
rom\-weaver\-probe \- Identify containers, patches, and known ROM headers
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBrom\-weaver probe\fR [\fB\-\-json\fR] [\fB\-\-select\fR] [\fB\-\-progress\fR] [\fB\-\-rom\-filter\fR] [\fB\-\-no\-progress\fR] [\fB\-\-patch\-filter\fR] [\fB\-\-log\-level\fR] [\fB\-\-no\-extract\fR] [\fB\-\-no\-ignore\fR] [\fB\-v\fR|\fB\-\-verbose\fR]... [\fB\-q\fR|\fB\-\-quiet\fR] [\fB\-\-dep\-trace\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] <\fISOURCE\fR>
.SH DESCRIPTION
Identify containers, patches, and known ROM headers
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-json\fR
Emit progress and terminal status as JSON lines
.TP
\fB\-\-select\fR \fI<SELECT>\fR
Select an extracted probe payload by exact name, prefix, or glob (repeatable)
.TP
\fB\-\-progress\fR
Force running progress events on
.TP
\fB\-\-rom\-filter\fR
Keep ROM\-like payload candidates during automatic extraction
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-progress\fR
Disable running progress events
.TP
\fB\-\-patch\-filter\fR
Keep patch\-like payload candidates during automatic extraction
.TP
\fB\-\-log\-level\fR \fI<LOG_LEVEL>\fR
Set application log level (off, error, warn, info, debug, trace)
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
off
.IP \(bu 2
error
.IP \(bu 2
warn
.IP \(bu 2
info
.IP \(bu 2
debug
.IP \(bu 2
trace
.RE
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-extract\fR
Disable container auto\-extract and probe the source bytes directly
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-ignore\fR
Disable default ignore filtering during probe container payload resolution
.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-verbose\fR
Increase application log verbosity; repeat for debug and trace
.TP
\fB\-q\fR, \fB\-\-quiet\fR
Show only application errors
.TP
\fB\-\-dep\-trace\fR
Enable trace logs from dependencies (for example nod)
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.TP
<\fISOURCE\fR>
File or container to inspect
